Rating: 3
Not sure why some folks had their knickers in a twist over 3 pots plus a casserole dish, but oh well! Double the garlic and cinnamon and fish the garlic and clove out of the cheese sauce. Use good feta. If you don't have access to a Mediterranean market, there is a good feta available at Costco (Dodoni brand) Any tube pasta will work (like ziti), just be sure to undercook it - to less than al dente - because it cooks more in the oven. Use Japanese eggplants (the long slender ones) because the skin is more tender, hence no peeling. I love Greek food. I used disposable foil pans so I could make two (each for three people) and froze the other, so I hope it comes out well when baked from frozen.

