This is a staple at my house. My supermarket doesn't always carry ground lamb, so when I see it I buy extra to keep in the freezer to make this. My few alterations: brown the meat first and add spices to the meat, eliminate the sugar (use a big, sweet onion instead)for the meat sauce;use a dash of ground clove (carefully - it can be overpowering) and finely mince the garlic in the cheese sauce. This is a bit labor intensive and you'll end up with a lot of dirty dishes; but I find it no more work than making lasagna and the results are far more flavorful. Make this, you'll love it!

