Rating: 0
This dish was incorrectly named pastitsio. The correct name for this dish is mousaka as seen in any greek restuarant and even by the definition in the food dictionary on this website: mousaka [MOO-sah-kah] Originally from Greece, moussaka is a popular dish throughout most of the Near East. Its basic form consists of sliced eggplant and ground lamb or beef that are layered, then baked. The variations, however, are endless and the dish is often covered with a BÉCHAMEL sauce enriched with eggs and/or cheese.

